  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">International Alert expects to deliver on activities such as:  

 Work with MAG management to integrate conflict sensitivity into existing MAG tools, frameworks, etc and build new tools and frameworks if necessary (i.e. a Conflict Sensitivity Strategy, etc) 

Assist programme implementation teams at every stage of the programme cycle (i.e. project design, implementation and/or monitoring) as well as senior management at the strategic decision-making level  

Review proposals, quarterly reports, annual review reports, and evaluation reports from MAG country teams and implementing partners to support the learning around conflict sensitivity or build awareness around conflict sensitive/insensitivities 

Provide direct support to assessing project proposals, upcoming bid proposals, etc for the conflict sensitivity of the action and make recommendations for supporting more conflict sensitive proposed action (if necessary)  

Prepare to second Conflict Sensitivity Advisors to Country Programmes for short term support to implementation (if necessary) 

Support theory of change and results framework development for MAG colleagues and provide practical advice on improving the conflict sensitivity of indicators and any M&amp;E methodology 

Review MAG country strategies and provide practical advice/recommendations on how to integrate conflict sensitivity throughout all programming strands</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">International Alert will provide a Conflict Sensitivity Helpdesk for MAG to support the organizational approach to conflict sensitivity. This helpdesk will provide practical advice in a timely manner which is tailored to support the staff, suitable to anyone aiming to improve conflict sensitivity, drawing on real examples to illustrate solutions to common dilemmas through an extended period of accompaniment to the staff and operations teams in country and headquarters through the development, management, and monitoring of upcoming and current programmes/projects in FCAS contexts.</narrative>
  </description>
